==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|la}}

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Scandinavian, compare with Swedish ''[[blöja]]'' "diaper". The original meaning was probably "cloth" whence "[[trousseau]]" on the Finnic side and finally "gift".

===Noun===
'''lahja'''

# [[present]], [[gift]].
# (''figurative'') [[talent]], [[gift]]

